<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="mind-v">mind <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /maɪnd/    美 /maɪnd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[不用于进行时和被动语态；常用于疑问句或否定句] 介意；在乎</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Would you like tea or coffee? 
你是喜欢喝茶还是咖啡？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— I don’t mind — either is fine. 
我无所谓，什么都行。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>Would you mind if</strong> I opened the window? 
我打开窗户你介意吗？</p></div>

<ul>
<li>mind (sb / sth) doing sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I don’t mind letting you read my poem.  
我不介意让你读读我的诗。</p><footer>外研⑧ – 6</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Do you mind me / my smoking here? 
我在这儿抽烟，你介意吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Yes, I do mind. / No, go ahead.
是的，我很介意。/不介意，你抽吧。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>mind + that / wh- 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My parents don’t mind what job I do as long as I am happy. 
我父母不介意我做什么工作，只要我高兴就行。</p><footer>2009 湖北</footer></div>

<h4 id="2-watch-look-after">2.<strong>注意；小心 (watch)；照看 (look after)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The restaurant was full of people, I moved slowly minding every step. 
餐馆里到处都是人，我小心翼翼地挪动着步子。</p><footer> 2008 全国改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Could you mind my bag for a moment? 
你介意帮我看一会儿包吗？</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="mind-your-own-business">mind your own business</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[非正式用语] 别管闲事：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Why don’t you just mind your own business and leave me in peace?
你为什么就不能别管闲事，让我清静一下呢？</p></div>

<h3 id="never-mind">Never mind.</h3>
<p>1.<strong>不要紧。/ 没关系。</strong>  </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>— Is Peter coming?
— No, he <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (改变了主意) after a phone call at the last minute.  （2015 重庆改）  </li>
<li>— Sorry I’m late. I got stuck in traffic.
— <strong><em>_</em></strong>_. You’re here now. Come in and sit down.  （2012 山东）<br />
A.You are welcome <br />
B.That’s right<br />
C. I have no idea<br />
D.Never mind  </li>
<li>Why don’t you just <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (别管闲事) and leave me alone?  （2007 全国改）  </li>
<li>He and his wife are<strong><em>_</em></strong>_ the same mind; they both want their son to go to college.  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. changed his mind  2. D  3. mind your own business  4. of  </p></div>